<h1 class="doc-page-title">COMPASS User guide</h1>
<p class="doc-page-lead">This guide provides step-by-step instructions for common tasks and user journeys in COMPASS.</p>

<h2 id="getting-started">Getting started</h2>
                
                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Signing in</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>Navigate to the COMPASS URL in your web browser</li>
                    <li>Click the "Sign in" button</li>
                    <li>Enter your DfE email address and password</li>
                    <li>Complete multi-factor authentication if prompted</li>
                    <li>You will be redirected to the COMPASS home page</li>
                </ol>

                <div class="alert alert-info">
                    <p class="mb-0"><i class="fas fa-info-circle"></i> You must have a DfE email address and Azure Entra ID account to access COMPASS.</p>
                </div>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">First-time setup</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>Review your user profile by clicking the user icon in the top navigation</li>
                    <li>Set your notification preferences in "My settings"</li>
                    <li>Familiarise yourself with the main navigation menu on the left sidebar</li>
                    <li>Explore the home dashboard to see recent activity</li>
                </ol>

                <hr class="my-4">

                <h2 id="navigation">Navigating COMPASS</h2>
                
                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Main navigation</h3>
                <p>The left sidebar provides access to all major sections:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Home:</strong> Dashboard with overview and recent activity</li>
                    <li><strong>Product reporting:</strong> Submit and view product performance metrics</li>
                    <li><strong>Enterprise reporting:</strong> Enterprise metrics and functional standards</li>
                    <li><strong>Reports:</strong> RAID reports and analysis</li>
                    <li><strong>Product governance:</strong> Products, risks, issues, milestones, and actions</li>
                    <li><strong>Administration:</strong> System settings and user management (administrators only)</li>
                </ul>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Top navigation</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Home:</strong> Return to the home page</li>
                    <li><strong>Documentation:</strong> Access this documentation</li>
                    <li><strong>Help:</strong> Help resources and support information</li>
                    <li><strong>Dark mode toggle:</strong> Switch between light and dark themes</li>
                    <li><strong>User menu:</strong> Access your settings and profile</li>
                </ul>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Breadcrumbs</h3>
                <p>Use the breadcrumb navigation at the top of each page to understand your location in the system and quickly navigate back to parent pages.</p>

                <hr class="my-4">

                <h2 id="risks">Managing risks</h2>
                
                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Creating a risk</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>Navigate to <strong>Risks</strong> in the sidebar menu</li>
                    <li>Click the <strong>"Create new risk"</strong> button</li>
                    <li>Complete the risk form:
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>Title:</strong> Brief, descriptive title for the risk</li>
                            <li><strong>Description:</strong> Detailed description of the risk</li>
                            <li><strong>Product:</strong> Select the product(s) affected by this risk</li>
                            <li><strong>Risk types:</strong> Select one or more risk categories (strategic, operational, financial, etc.)</li>
                            <li><strong>Risk tier:</strong> Select the appropriate tier (product, programme, portfolio, enterprise)</li>
                            <li><strong>Impact:</strong> Rate the potential impact (1-5, where 5 is highest)</li>
                            <li><strong>Likelihood:</strong> Rate the likelihood of occurrence (1-5, where 5 is highest)</li>
                            <li><strong>Risk owner:</strong> Search and assign a risk owner</li>
                            <li><strong>Status:</strong> Set the initial status (typically "Open")</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li>Click <strong>"Create"</strong> to save the risk</li>
                </ol>

                <div class="card border-primary mt-3 mb-3">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <h4 class="h6"><i class="fas fa-lightbulb text-warning"></i> Best practice</h4>
                        <p class="mb-0">The risk score is automatically calculated as Impact × Likelihood. Focus on accurately assessing both dimensions to ensure proper prioritisation.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Viewing and editing risks</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>Navigate to <strong>Risks</strong> in the sidebar menu</li>
                    <li>Use the search or filter options to find a specific risk</li>
                    <li>Click on a risk to view its details</li>
                    <li>Click <strong>"Edit"</strong> to modify the risk</li>
                    <li>Update the fields as needed</li>
                    <li>Click <strong>"Save"</strong> to save your changes</li>
                </ol>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Linking actions to risks</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>Open the risk you want to add actions to</li>
                    <li>Scroll to the <strong>"Actions"</strong> section</li>
                    <li>Click <strong>"Add action"</strong></li>
                    <li>Either create a new action or link an existing action</li>
                    <li>The action will now appear in the risk's actions list</li>
                </ol>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Closing risks</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>Open the risk you want to close</li>
                    <li>Update the status to "Closed"</li>
                    <li>Add a closure note explaining why the risk is being closed</li>
                    <li>Save the changes</li>
                </ol>

                <hr class="my-4">

                <h2 id="issues">Managing issues</h2>
                
                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Creating an issue</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>Navigate to <strong>Issues</strong> in the sidebar menu</li>
                    <li>Click the <strong>"Create new issue"</strong> button</li>
                    <li>Complete the issue form:
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>Title:</strong> Brief, descriptive title for the issue</li>
                            <li><strong>Description:</strong> Detailed description of the issue</li>
                            <li><strong>Product:</strong> Select the product(s) affected</li>
                            <li><strong>Priority:</strong> Set the priority level (low, medium, high, critical)</li>
                            <li><strong>Severity:</strong> Rate the impact of the issue</li>
                            <li><strong>Issue owner:</strong> Assign an owner responsible for resolution</li>
                            <li><strong>Status:</strong> Set the initial status (typically "Open")</li>
                            <li><strong>Target resolution date:</strong> Set when the issue should be resolved</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li>Click <strong>"Create"</strong> to save the issue</li>
                </ol>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Tracking issue resolution</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>Open the issue you're working on</li>
                    <li>Update the status as work progresses (Open → In Progress → Resolved → Closed)</li>
                    <li>Add regular updates in the notes section</li>
                    <li>Link related actions that contribute to resolution</li>
                    <li>When resolved, update the status and add resolution details</li>
                </ol>

                <hr class="my-4">

                <h2 id="actions">Managing actions</h2>
                
                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Creating an action</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>Navigate to <strong>Actions</strong> in the sidebar menu</li>
                    <li>Click the <strong>"Create new action"</strong> button</li>
                    <li>Complete the action form:
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>Title:</strong> Clear, actionable title</li>
                            <li><strong>Description:</strong> Detailed description of what needs to be done</li>
                            <li><strong>Action owner:</strong> Assign the person responsible</li>
                            <li><strong>Action source:</strong> Select the source (risk, issue, meeting, decision, etc.)</li>
                            <li><strong>Due date:</strong> Set when the action should be completed</li>
                            <li><strong>Status:</strong> Set the initial status (typically "Not started")</li>
                            <li><strong>Priority:</strong> Set the priority level</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li>Optionally link the action to related risks, issues, or milestones</li>
                    <li>Click <strong>"Create"</strong> to save the action</li>
                </ol>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Updating action status</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>Navigate to <strong>Actions</strong></li>
                    <li>Click on the action to open it</li>
                    <li>Update the status (Not started → In progress → Complete)</li>
                    <li>Add progress notes as needed</li>
                    <li>If the action is complete, add completion notes</li>
                    <li>Save your changes</li>
                </ol>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Viewing your actions</h3>
                <p>To see all actions assigned to you:</p>
                <ol>
                    <li>Navigate to <strong>Actions</strong></li>
                    <li>Use the filter to select "My actions" or filter by your name</li>
                    <li>Sort by due date to prioritise your work</li>
                </ol>

                <hr class="my-4">

                <h2 id="milestones">Tracking milestones</h2>
                
                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Creating a milestone</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>Navigate to <strong>Milestones</strong> in the sidebar menu</li>
                    <li>Click the <strong>"Create new milestone"</strong> button</li>
                    <li>Complete the milestone form:
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>Title:</strong> Clear milestone name</li>
                            <li><strong>Description:</strong> What the milestone represents</li>
                            <li><strong>Product:</strong> Select the associated product</li>
                            <li><strong>Target date:</strong> When the milestone should be achieved</li>
                            <li><strong>Status:</strong> Set the current status (Not started, In progress, Achieved, etc.)</li>
                            <li><strong>Milestone owner:</strong> Assign a responsible person</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li>Click <strong>"Create"</strong> to save the milestone</li>
                </ol>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Linking RAID items to milestones</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>Open the milestone</li>
                    <li>Navigate to the relevant section (Risks, Issues, or Actions)</li>
                    <li>Click <strong>"Link existing"</strong> or <strong>"Create new"</strong></li>
                    <li>Select or create the item to link</li>
                    <li>The linked items will appear in the milestone view</li>
                </ol>

                <hr class="my-4">

                <h2 id="metrics">Submitting performance metrics</h2>
                
                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Product performance metrics</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>Navigate to <strong>Product reporting → Performance metrics</strong></li>
                    <li>Select your product from the list</li>
                    <li>Click <strong>"Submit metrics"</strong></li>
                    <li>Enter values for each metric:
                        <ul>
                            <li>Actual value</li>
                            <li>Target value (if applicable)</li>
                            <li>Reporting period</li>
                            <li>Notes or commentary</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li>Click <strong>"Submit"</strong> to save the metrics</li>
                </ol>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Enterprise metrics</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>Navigate to <strong>Enterprise reporting → Enterprise metrics</strong></li>
                    <li>Click <strong>"Submit metrics"</strong></li>
                    <li>Complete the enterprise metrics form</li>
                    <li>Add any relevant notes or context</li>
                    <li>Click <strong>"Submit"</strong> to save</li>
                </ol>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Viewing metric history</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>Navigate to the relevant metrics page</li>
                    <li>Select your product or metric</li>
                    <li>Click <strong>"View history"</strong></li>
                    <li>View the trend chart and historical data table</li>
                    <li>Use filters to adjust the time period shown</li>
                </ol>

                <hr class="my-4">

                <h2 id="assessments">Conducting functional standards assessments</h2>
                
                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Starting an assessment</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>Navigate to <strong>Enterprise reporting → Functional standards</strong></li>
                    <li>Click <strong>"Conduct assessment"</strong></li>
                    <li>Select the product being assessed</li>
                    <li>Select the functional standard to assess against</li>
                    <li>Click <strong>"Begin assessment"</strong></li>
                </ol>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Completing the assessment</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>Review each criterion in the selected standard</li>
                    <li>For each criterion:
                        <ul>
                            <li>Read the criterion description</li>
                            <li>Select a compliance level (Not met, Partially met, Fully met)</li>
                            <li>Provide evidence of compliance</li>
                            <li>Add notes or explanations</li>
                            <li>Attach supporting documentation if needed</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li>Review your assessment</li>
                    <li>Click <strong>"Submit assessment"</strong> to save</li>
                </ol>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Viewing assessment history</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>Navigate to <strong>Functional standards</strong></li>
                    <li>Select a product</li>
                    <li>View the list of completed assessments</li>
                    <li>Click on an assessment to view details</li>
                    <li>Compare assessments over time to track compliance improvements</li>
                </ol>

                <hr class="my-4">

                <h2 id="reports">Viewing reports</h2>
                
                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Risks and issues report</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>Navigate to <strong>Reports → Risks and issues</strong></li>
                    <li>Use the filters to refine the report:
                        <ul>
                            <li>Filter by product</li>
                            <li>Filter by status</li>
                            <li>Filter by date range</li>
                            <li>Filter by owner</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li>Sort columns by clicking the column headers</li>
                    <li>Click <strong>"Export"</strong> to download the report</li>
                </ol>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Analysis report</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>Navigate to <strong>Reports → Analysis</strong></li>
                    <li>View visual analysis of RAID data</li>
                    <li>Explore charts showing:
                        <ul>
                            <li>Risk distribution by type</li>
                            <li>Issue status breakdown</li>
                            <li>Action completion rates</li>
                            <li>Trend analysis over time</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li>Use filters to adjust the analysis scope</li>
                    <li>Export charts and data as needed</li>
                </ol>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Product dashboard</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>Navigate to <strong>Products</strong></li>
                    <li>Select a product from the list</li>
                    <li>View the comprehensive product dashboard showing:
                        <ul>
                            <li>Product information and status</li>
                            <li>Active RAID items</li>
                            <li>Recent metrics submissions</li>
                            <li>Functional standards assessments</li>
                            <li>Upcoming milestones</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li>Click on any section to view more details</li>
                </ol>

                <hr class="my-4">

